org.apache.wicket.extensions.breadcrumb
Interface IBreadCrumbParticipant

All Superinterfaces:
IClusterable, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BreadCrumbPanel, BreadCrumbParticipantDelegate, FirstPanel, FourthPanel, ResultPanel, SecondPanel, ThirdPanel
public interface IBreadCrumbParticipant
extends IClusterable

Bread crumb participants function as proxies for components that are part of a bread crumb hierarchy. An example of a bread crumb is: 

     Home > Products & Solutions > Hardware > Desktop Systems
In a panel based implementation, Home, Products & Solutions etc would be seperate panels that all are bread crumb participants: for instance the Home participant's title would return 'Home', and the component would be the corresponding panel.

Author:
Eelco Hillenius
